ForwardByKey

Iterates over all keys in sort order. Retrieves each key's first duplicate record in duplicate sort order. One can iterate over the duplicate records separately in a nested loop with ValuesForward or ValuesReverse, or one can iterate including duplicate records with Forward.

GetNearest(KeyDataPair, out KeyDataPair)

Put(KeyDataPair, MultiValueCursorPutOption)

Store by cursor. This function stores key/data pairs into the database. The cursor is positioned at the new item, or on failure usually near it. Note: Earlier documentation incorrectly said errors would leave the state of the cursor unchanged.

Declaration
public bool Put(in KeyDataPair entry, MultiValueCursorPutOption option)
Parameters
Type Name Description
KeyDataPair entry
MultiValueCursorPutOption option
Returns
Type Description
Boolean
Remarks

true if inserted without error, false if NoDuplicateData was specified and the key/data pair already exists.
